Open a plain Command Prompt (cmd.exe) or Windows Terminal with a Command Prompt tab (not PowerShell ISE).


1. Run this exact command (adjust the path if needed):
"C:\Program Files\MySQL\MySQL Server 8.0\bin\mysql_config_editor.exe" ^  set --login-path=restore --host=localhost --user=root --port=3306 --password

When prompted:

Enter password:

Type your password (it will not show anything) and press Enter.

2. Verify it saved:

"C:\Program Files\MySQL\MySQL Server 8.0\bin\mysql_config_editor.exe" print --login-path=restore

3. Quick connection test using the login path:

"C:\Program Files\MySQL\MySQL Server 8.0\bin\mysql.exe" --login-path=restore -e "SELECT USER(), @@hostname, @@port;"Show more lines

If that prints a result, your login path is good.
